description.narrative: IR1.4: By 2018, all 207 developmental health zones of the PNDS plan, implement and follow the minimum and complementary packages of activities as defined in the PNDS and the 308 other health zones plan, implement and follow the minimum high impact package at the clinical and community levels., which contributes to Child Health, Health Systems Strengthening, Hiv Prevention, Maternal And Newborn Health, Protect, Care And Support Children And Families Affected By Hiv. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Advocacy And Public Engagement, Developing And Leveraging Resources And Partnerships, Operational Support To Programme Delivery, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: CHILD SURVIVALPCR1: By end 2018, the proportion of children, newborns, families who benefit from high health impact quality interventions, including HIV Prevention of Mother to Child Transmission (PMTCT), nutrition, and water - sanitation - hygiene (WASH ) increases significantly and fairly, particularly in health sub-divisions and communities.

description.narrative: In 2019, several evaluations showed progress in the health system, including the baseline study of Child Friendly Communities (CFC), the review of Improved Monitoring for Action and an evaluation of the post distribution of Long-Lasting Insecticidal Nets (LLIN). The findings were used to inform the the design of the next country programme (2020-2024). The evaluations of LLIN distribution revealed the effectiveness and the efficiency of two methods of distribution; community-based and school-based. Operational cost was reduced to $0.9 for the community-based approach and $1.5 for school-based. The MoH scaled up both approaches to other provinces in 2019. | Status:Met | As-of Date:07/02/2020
